{"id": "1440615889895690360", "channel_id": "1440566066483826788", "author_id": "452516689225973761", "author_name": "thpdom", "content": "It's all about the developers intended experience. Ig.\n\nEven the removed madness debuffs were first added in with some intension in mind. Like hp cacoons. As much as the community hated them. They allowed the bosses to actually showcase all their mechanics. And players were forced to play/think around them. And probably even unconsciously created experiences that are looked back on fondly. Rather then gacha game boss hp stick dies in a few hits.\n\nThis currently is the equitable to a irl remake of old Disney movies, where half of the intention feels lost in translation.\n\nArc 2 obviously doesn't face this issue purely because... Boss hp is massive. And everyone is expected to be endgame kitted out for it already.", "timestamp": "2025-11-19T08:13:13.500000+00:00", "thread_id": "1440566066483826788", "edited_timestamp": "2025-11-19T08:15:11.060000+00:00"}
