{"id": "1440545776072659036", "channel_id": "1440393579121082378", "author_id": "543447160302207006", "author_name": "mementosunrise", "content": "I agree. I only started playing this game recently because people were talking about it as one of the hardest gacha. For me it really was a fun experience, and I managed to finish 4 story chapters and 3 hard chapters before the patch. Yesterday I cleared Chapter 5 and it was braindead easy, even compared to the early chapters that basically serve as a tutorial. It’s not like I was using meta units with enlightenments either; I was mostly playing with standard characters without any dupes.\n\nI figured the real challenge would be in hard mode, but then I found out that it was heavily butchered as well. \n\nNgl, I’m disappointed, and it really killed my motivation to keep playing despite the very good story. There are plenty of gacha slops where you just turn on auto-battle and go make yourself a coffee without using your brain at all, probably around 99% of the market, but truly difficult and interesting games? I can barely name any.", "timestamp": "2025-11-19T03:34:37.062000+00:00", "type": 19, "thread_id": "1440393579121082378", "mentions": ["212587018436345856"], "reply_to": "1440526160436924520"}
